[32m+[m[32m## 5. Lessons learned[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### 5.1 What worked[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m1. **ADR-first, code-second.** ADR-031 (MADR format) was written *before*[m
[32m+[m[32m   the executor code. The decision matrix in the ADR forced honest[m
[32m+[m[32m   comparison of 8 candidates, and the consequence section made the[m
[32m+[m[32m   30/90-day review schedule non-optional.[m
[32m+[m[32m2. **Backwards-compat by default.** B2 shipped with `BIFROST_ENABLED=1`[m
[32m+[m[32m   gating. The first 48 hours of CI runs were identical to pre-Bifrost[m
[32m+[m[32m   behavior. No incident attribution problem.[m
[32m+[m[32m3. **Test pyramid was right.** 4 layers: unit (353 + 464 + 299 = 1,116[m
[32m+[m[32m   test lines), integration (L5-111 cache), shadow (B6 dispatcher gates[m
[32m+[m[32m   5% → 25% → 100%), operational (B7 playbook + B9 kill switch).[m
[32m+[m[32m4. **Fork-only policy held.** None of B1–B9 was upstreamed to[m
[32m+[m[32m   `diegosouzapw/OmniRoute`. The 4 files in PR #95 / #98 stay[m
[32m+[m[32m   KooshaPari/OmniRoute-local.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### 5.2 What didn't[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m1. **B8 deferred is a real gap.** The Bifrost MCP-client integration was[m
[32m+[m[32m   dropped in favor of substrate MCP work. The decision was made in[m
[32m+[m[32m   L5-118 cherry-pick post-mortem; we should re-evaluate B8 against the[m
[32m+[m[32m   substrate MCP work to see if it can ride on the same substrate.[m
[32m+[m[32m2. **PR #95 / #97 contamination.** The original B9 PR (#95) and the[m
[32m+[m[32m   re-do (#97) were both closed because of cherry-pick contamination[m
[32m+[m[32m   (cross-fork ref divergence). The clean re-do is #98, which is OPEN[m
[32m+[m[32m   as of this worklog. **#98 must merge before B9 is "done"** — it is[m
[32m+[m[32m   the only path that wires the kill switch into the executor.[m
[32m+[m[32m3. **No live traffic measurement yet.** B6 is merged, but the dispatcher[m
[32m+[m[32m   has not been turned on in production. The 30-day review (2026-07-19)[m
[32m+[m[32m   will have no data point to compare until someone flips the switch.[m
[32m+[m[32m4. **The `vendor/bifrost/` copy in this repo is still empty** (only[m
[32m+[m[32m   `VENDOR.md` + `.gitkeep`). ADR-031 said vendored; we have not vendored.[m
